DBAG_Long Description:
CGSS Custody System provides the full range of functions to CGSS operations and customers to trade; settle; and manage hedge and investment funds. The functions are provided across six major systems: 
·	CCS & CCS Online providing core custody services; 
·	CFN providing client transaction and reporting; 
·	CDS providing reference data management; 
·	CDOC providing STP processing of statements; and Corona providing security and cash reconciliation.
 
CCS and CCS online (JCCS) are the core custody systems used by CGSS Operations providing Front Office; Settlement; Transfers; Corporate Action Management; Fee processing; and Securities reference date. Detailed services include:
·	Front Office: Trade import – Swift, CFN, XML; Trade Entry & Maintenance; Trade Enrichment; Calculation; of Trade Dates; SWIFT MT 5x messages; Inquiries and Reports;
·	Settlement: Trade build; Price build; Settlement build; Preliminary and final confirmation; Contract note matching;
·	Transfers: Trade entry; maintenance & build; Queue management; Communication to client and fund by Fax and SWIFT; Contract note matching;
·	Corporate Action Management: Batch creation and maintenance; Authorization and notifications;
Communication with customers and participants is support with SWIFT FIN and MX messages; Fax and Email.

CDS allows CGGS Data Management team to manage hedge and investment fund reference data by combining input from external vendor feeds, internal system feeds, and from direct user input. The reference data managed includes:
·	Create and update of security master and populating general data for all securities and specific data based on 3rd party vendor data feeds;
·	Creates corporate actions of numerous types, including dividends, splits, name changes, based on data received from IDC and Telekurs;
·	Update of financial instrument prices throughout the business day from external vendors such as Telekurs and IDC and internal systems Corona);
·	Transfer of security master; prices and corporate action back to from CDS to CCS using “Bundling” mechanism of reference data changes.

CGSS Funds Net (CFN) is the real-time communication and trading platform for financial institution customers. Major functions include:
·	Transactions Placement;
·	Corporate Action Notification and Confirmations;
·	Fund Information incl. asset objectives and rules, asset set-up request, and pricing;
·	Client reporting;
·	Transaction status updates, ageing, documents and tracing information;
